<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-08-26T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-08-26T10:00:00-05:00" n="712" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/72: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-26T11:00:00-04:00">August 26, 1930—11
                                a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>34. 1. Department approves effort to obtain guarantee referred to in last
                            paragraph of your despatch No. 67, August 5.</p>
                        <p>2. Please keep Department informed by telegraph.</p>
                        <p>3. Should you be unable to persuade the Austrian Government to accept
                            Senate reservation without reduction of term of treaty, would <pb facs="0971" n="857" xml:id="pg_857"/> you favor asking for such
                            acceptance even if accompanied by limitation of compulsory term to
                            1935?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>